Torque Server
-------------

torque-server is a Go library to create an HTTP service to broadcast data backed
in a key/value datastore under a fixed time update policy. Think of it as a
front-line cache for rapidly changing data.


In this diagram

                                                              +-----------------
                                                              | HTTP(S) clients
                                                              |
             Update data in fixed intervals                   |
+-----------------+                +------------------+<------+
| Key/Value Store |   (1s/1m/1h)   |  torque service  |<------+
|                 +--------------->|                  |<------+
|                 |<---------------+                  |<------+
+-----------------+                |                  |<------+
                                   +------------------+<------+
                                                              |
                                                              |
                                                              +-----------------

